messages.content: Thank god Polaris remembered to put on some damn *clothes* before he left the house. It’s.. cold out. He stuffed his hands in his pants pockets, his ripped hat sitting carefully on his head. “I didn’t get your disc when I grabbed the bag a month ago?” he asks Nexum as they walk, ignoring the girls who ocassionally think about his ass. He’s *never* going to get used to it.

Nexum was sitting on Duvet, as usual. 
She sighed "No, the *bastard* Kept it for himself, somewhere. Wasn't in his stupid bag" She stick her tongue out, with a look of *disgust*. She was carefully holding the bat, who was *more than likely* stolen.

“Hm.”
That.. makes him a little depressed. And mad at himself. How long as she been without her disc..? How hadn’t he caught on that those weren’t the only discs..? He shakes his head. No point in worrying about it now. He’ll apologize once they get the disc back.

"*God* I can't wait to see him and just-" she swung her bat angrily, almost falling off Duvet. 
She was *very* pissed at Castus, she *did* want her memories back, but now ? Mudering him was almost her new top priority.
Star Platinum appeared, holding out it’s hands to catch Nexum in case she fell. “Worry about your discs, first.”
She was surprised by Star catching her and nodded rolling her eyes "Yeah...I guess you're right..."

“...”
What was this... balling feeling in his chest? He slowed to a stop, looking around. There were so many people... it was making him nervous. Someone here’s...

Nexum looked at him "Are you... Ok ?" Duvet has stopped as well, its instinct was *also* feeling that something was... *off*

Superbia was walking along Castus, grinning as she spotted the two from the crowd *perfect*. She whispered *"Castus look ! it's them ! finally !"*
"Is this the part where I....flip the script?"
“...Get behind me,” he says to Nexum, standing in front of her and Duvet, Star Platinum back on his side.

"What ? what's wrong ? " She started to get confused, Duvet instantly went behind him.

Superbia cackled madly "Do asr you wish !~" Her stand manifested, holding her and flying up high, gently landing her a few feets away from Polaris and Nexum. 
"Greetings !" She bowed "I'm glad to *finally* meet you again, Nexum"
“I SAID *GET THE FUCK BEHIND ME!*” he shouts, Star Platinum moving forward and launching fast punches to where Superbia landed.
The ground
is tilting

*Shit*
“*EVERYBODY GET INSIDE!*” he shouts to the surrounding poeple, who have begun to panic and try to run away.
A confused old lady couldnt tell what was happening

Duvet stayed behind Polaris, Nexum was starting to get... anxious *god. that wasn't good*

Superbia's stand managed to lift her up *right* before any punches landed, and she gasped "My my, what a *rude* way to welcome someone ! oh well ~" Seeing the ground tilting, she waited a bit in the air.

“*Shit.* Nexum, go help the people who aren’t inside!” he shouted again, launching himself up into the air with Star and grasping his hands together, overlapping them with Star’s and slamming them down onto Superbia.

"But not fast enough."

Of course, it won’t kill him, that’s not how Mun’s work, but... He’s a little out of it. Everything is ringing, and he can barely here himself groaning in pain as he pushes himself up a little while away from Castus.

Once Nexum has calmed down, she took a deep breath and made Duvet rushed to Polaris and Castus *Fuck it. FUCK IT*

“You f-fuckin... *bastard...—*” he mumbles, groggily reaching a hand out to Castus before his vision turns to white. He pushes himself onto his feet, standing shakily. He’s okay. *He’s okay.* He just needs to walk this off. He’ll.. he’ll heal.
*..Where the fuck am I..?*

All that Polaris could see was an empty white nothingness, everything was white... and it seemed to go on and on.... 

Meanwhile, outside, Nexum made Duvet get as close to Castus as possible, and she hit him as *Hard* as she could in his head. She was still breathing fast, and was still scared, but she was also very *pissed*

“...”

He looks up, turning his head around to search for her.
“Show yourself.”

However, after a while, a tall, thin silouhette appeared in the distance.

“...”
He heads towards the silhouette. There’s something.. strangely familiar about him, strangely *terrifying* about him. Something he can’t put his finger on.
The feeling gets shoved down, and he approaches.
"There's no time like the present." he reaches into his pocket
